<emphasis id="B951E127FFC7C84E66FAF9CEFE89FC0A" bold="true" box="[199,328,902,928]" pageId="1" pageNumber="185">Etymology</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2546B6FFC7C84E676AF9CFFE29FC0A" authorityName="González" authorityYear="2021" box="[343,488,903,928]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Buestanmyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951E127FFC7C84E676AF9CFFE29FC0A" box="[343,488,903,928]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="185">Buestanmyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been named is to honor of the Ecuadorian horsefly specialist Dr. Jaime Buestán for his contribution to the knowledge of the family in the Neotropical region.
</paragraph>
